title: For Sale:  Enfield no4 mk2
postcontent:
Enfield rifle manufactured by Fazakerley - the finish is original, a type of baked on paint system that was invented by the British - other times known as Suncorite. According to website, the No4 Mk II (or Mk2) was adopted in 1949, with production at ROF-Fazakerley in July, 1949 until 1955. Fazakerley was the only plant to manufacture the No4 Mk2. fairly rare specimen and one to be proud of. The biggest difference in the MK2 and the MK1 is that the trigger of the MK2 is pinned to the receiver instead of the trigger guard. 
Good smooth metal no rust or pitting. beautiful wood no cracks and action and barrel are perfectly bedded in stock., original brass butt plate and original finish on wood. Good strong shiny bore. Nice specimen!

Will sell outright or trade for a browning 1911 22lr pistol.

This is a new Beretta A400 XPlor Kick Off 12ga Shotgun with a 26" barrel. This gun features absolutely beautiful wood, the grain is simply stunning! Shotgun was assembled for these photos so any glare on the wood or receiver is from the factory packing oils. 

The A400 Xcel is a 12-gauge competition shotgun that is faster-cycling, softer-shooting and better balanced than anything else on the market. Built on the revolutionary A400 action, it delivers follow-up shots 36% faster than any other brand, while its advanced recoil-reducing systems make it absolutely pleasant to shoot. Its sleek lines and superior ergonomics are designed with one goal in mind: letting the A400 naturally follow your eye to the target. It feeds reliably all types of shells from 2 ¾” to 3,” with loads ranging from target-light to hard hitting--making it also suited for the occasional upland or waterfowl hunt. Also, it features the unique Blink technology, a gas-operating system that is capable of delivering two shots in less than half a second, while also integrating an easy-maintenance self-cleaning piston. Furthermore, the action has sleek lines and a low profile, meaning that the vertical distance between the dominant eye and the supporting hand is reduced to a minimum. The result? A gun that follows your swing like an extension of your body and eyesight. There are no two ways about it: felt recoil is only a liability and the less of it, the better. This A400 XPlor incorporates Beretta's revolutionary Kick-Off recoil-reducing system operating to make recoil virtually negligible (70% overall reduction). It has a hydraulic shock absorber that softens the rearward energy from the action’s moving parts, which minimizes felt recoil while reducing wear within the receiver while neutralizing the recoil generated by the power of the cartridge. Also, the A400 is designed to recoil parallel to the comb, meaning no thump to the cheek and minimal muzzle rise. The A400 XPlor's cold-hammer forged barrel is made of nickel-chromium-molybdenum steel (Beretta’s “Steelium”), a proprietary formula engineered for consistency, toughness and durability. The bore is chrome-plated to facilitate cleaning and minimize wear and corrosion. And the new Optimabore HP choke tubes are particularly easy to remove--even after several thousands of rounds. title: For Sale:  NORWEGIAN m. 1914 Colt license Kongsberg Norwegian Colt 1911 .45 cal. 11.25mm
postcontent: This is original example of this classic military pistol. This was the first licensed copy of the Colt 1911 .45 pistol. Norway began production in their own factory after purchasing 728 pistols from the Colt factory between 1911 and 1917. During WW II, production of the pistol was continued under Nazi occupation up to 1945. This pistol is serial number 13825, designated model 1914, and manufactured in 1927, with all matching numbered small parts, including the distinctive extended slide stop. Finish is the original blue, possible arsenal refinished at one time. Grips are the original double diamond Norwegian grips said to be made of birch wood. RARE original Norwegian nickel magazine with correct black painted base.
